cs.CE, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.MS, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper proposes a machine learning based material modelling framework for elasticity and plasticity, which is relevant to computational engineering.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses machine learning tools to develop the material models, specifically Feed forward Neural Network (FNN) and Proper Orthogonal Decomposition Feed forward Neural Network (PODFNN).
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper applies the machine learning based material model in finite element analysis, which is a numerical method for solving partial differential equations.
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper uses the automatic symbolic differentiation tool AceGen to derive the tangent matrix for the finite element analysis, which is a mathematical software tool.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a novel method for developing the plasticity model using Proper Orthogonal Decomposition, which can improve the training performance and reduce the training time, which is relevant to software engineering.
